---
description: Keep assertion tests grouped and consistently named
globs: src/tests/**/*.cs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Test Suite Structure

- Do not create or extend generic catch-all test suites (for example `Extended*`, `Misc*`, `General*`).
- Put tests in assertion-group suites only (`StringAssertionTests`, `CollectionAssertionTests`, `DictionaryAssertionTests`, etc.).
- Keep one assertion group per test file, and make the file name match the suite name exactly.
- When adding a new assertion group, create a dedicated `*AssertionTests.cs` file for it.

# Test Naming Convention

- Test class names must follow: `<Group>AssertionTests`.
- Test method names must follow: `<MethodUnderTest>_When<Condition>_Should<ExpectedOutcome>`.
- Keep the same naming style when adding failure and success-path tests for new assertions.
